The Kansas City Black Pilots of America cordially invite aviation enthusiasts and the local community to an exclusive Meet and Greet event, taking place at the IMKC Store, located at 8600 Ward Parkway, on Saturday, Jan. 6th, 2024. 12pm - 3pm
Hosted by future B-2 Bomber pilot Rafael Edwin, this event promises an engaging experience for attendees to meet and interact with accomplished black pilots who have made significant contributions to the aviation industry. Guests will have the unique opportunity to learn about their inspiring journeys, ask questions, and gain insights into the world of aviation.
The event will also feature a photo session and autograph signing, allowing attendees to capture memorable moments with these trailblazing aviators. Whether you’re a seasoned aviation enthusiast or just curious about the world above the clouds, this Meet and Greet is an excellent opportunity to connect with passionate individuals who have soared to great heights in their aviation careers.
Details at a glance:
	•	Date: Saturday, Jan. 6th, 2024
	•	Time: 12pm-3pm
	•	Location: IMKC Store, 8600 Ward Parkway, Kansas City, MO
 •  Enter on the State Line side ( West side of Mall between Firehouse Subs and Five Below ) 
Don’t miss this chance to be part of an exciting event celebrating diversity and excellence in aviation. Join us for a day of inspiration and camaraderie at the Kansas City Black Pilots of America Meet and Greet.
The @kcbpa Meet and Greet at the @imkcstorekc @wardparkwaycenter location was beyond a success! Television coverage from @kshb41 @kmbc9news @fox4kc and @kctv5!
